<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7435> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7435" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Monetalis. In MRR 2.439, and Index, 561, refer also to Crawford, RRC 1.405-406, no. 391, 75 B.C. Probably a younger brother of the juror in the trial of Oppianicus (RE no. 2, above), and known to Cicero (Att. 13.34 and 45). See Shackleton Bailey, Studies 36; Syme, Historia 4, 1955, 61?RP 1.280-281.\n" .
